external_knowledge:
- 'young adults' refers to individuals aged between 18 and 29;
- 'Hispanic shores of Europe' indicates the region named Europe and ethnicity Hispanic;
- 'financial tides are not in the high currents' means the income level is not classified as 'High';
- 'year's clock ticked to 2017' indicates the year of the data is 2017.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT h.region_id, i.issue_name
FROM health_statistics h
JOIN health_issues i ON h.issue_id = i.issue_id;

SELECT *
FROM health_statistics
WHERE value > (
  SELECT AVG(value) 
  FROM health_statistics
);

external_knowledge:
- "waves" metaphorically represents health statistics records where each wave symbolizes a unique record (`stat_id`).;
- "seas of female health" metaphorically refers to females who are the subject of the health statistics (`sex_name = 'Female'`).;
- "the storm of hypertension" symbolizes the health issue of hypertension (`issue_name = 'Hypertension'`).;
- "lighthouses guiding these findings" refers to the data sources (`source_name`).;
- "years they were lit" refer to the years the data was recorded (`year`).;
- "scales on which the tempest's force was measured" metaphorically represents the unit measures (`measure_name`).

sql:
SELECT * 
FROM health_statistics 
ORDER BY year_id ASC;

external_knowledge:
- "younger bunch" refers to age groups with IDs less than 10;
- "less certain" refers to cases where the recorded value is less than the confidence interval;
- "unique ID" refers to the unique identifier for each health statistic record;
- "type of measurement used" is the measure name;
- "gender group" refers to the sex name;
- "location" is the region name;
- "observed number" is the recorded value;
- "uncertainty range" is the confidence interval.
